On 27 Jun 2002, George Lyle wrote:

> > On Wed, 26 Jun 2002, Nemo, the Bus Captain wrote:
> > > >>Looking at 185's vs. 195's on Tires for my 71
> > > Westy (1600cc).......Got the
> > > right tire it's just a matter of what width..
> > 
> > well for a little more stability and better (IMO) handling you could 
> > 205/70R14 tires...they are almost identical in outside diameter to 
> > stock 185/14 tires that are stock.
> 
> One other thing to think about is that early bays have the worm-and-
> peg steering box that is weaker than the later worm-and-roller box.  

but Bentley says  that the worm and peg is bigger and stronger than the
previous units starting in 1968  

> Unfortunately, the two boxes do not interchange.  My theory is that 
> the increased steering effort of the radial tires over the original 
> narrow bias ply tires caused more steering box failures, prompting the 
> change.  For this reason, I've resisted the urge to go to wider tires 
> on my '71.  If you do make the switch, make sure you are moving before 
> steering to reduce stress on the peg.

I have not noticed significant differences between the 185 and 205 tires,
but it has been a long time since I used the narrow tires

Bob


